WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.130 --> 00:00:04.980
This is the rainforest of Panama,

00:00:04.980 --> 00:00:07.650
and these are American soldiers.

00:00:07.650 --> 00:00:09.390
They're back in the coastal country

00:00:09.390 --> 00:00:11.970
after a 25-year hiatus

00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:15.510
for jungle training
alongside Panamanian forces.

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:18.600
So why are they back now?

00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:22.440
For a long time we were
focused on many other things

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:24.120
and we forgot about our neighborhood.

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:26.550
What we are seeing with
President Trump is a refocus

00:00:26.550 --> 00:00:27.570
on the Western Hemisphere.

00:00:30.960 --> 00:00:34.620
The training is part of the
biggest US military buildup in

00:00:34.620 --> 00:00:37.380
Latin America in decades, and comes

00:00:37.380 --> 00:00:38.730
after the shock seizure

00:00:38.730 --> 00:00:41.820
of Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro.

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:45.120
Trump has clearly embraced what he sees

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:47.670
as a big success in Venezuela.

00:00:47.670 --> 00:00:51.540
He was able to take out
Nicolás Maduro with no loss

00:00:51.540 --> 00:00:53.490
of US soldiers' lives.

00:01:09.465 --> 00:01:11.340
Now, there are governments in the region

00:01:11.340 --> 00:01:12.510
that have backed Trump.

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:14.970
We saw in March a gathering in Miami

00:01:14.970 --> 00:01:18.450
of like-minded, right wing
Latin American leaders willing

00:01:18.450 --> 00:01:20.850
to partner with the US,
willing to coordinate,

00:01:20.850 --> 00:01:22.680
may be willing to submit, frankly.

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:25.050
- We come together to
announce a brand new military

00:01:25.050 --> 00:01:28.260
coalition to eradicate
the criminal cartels

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:29.280
plaguing our region.

00:01:31.260 --> 00:01:34.140
But there are many voices
who are opposed to this

00:01:34.140 --> 00:01:38.040
who do not think an expanded
US military presence is a

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:42.450
recipe for a stable,
prosperous Latin America.

00:02:00.450 --> 00:02:03.945
Alright, listen up. We're
gonna head to your survival

00:02:03.945 --> 00:02:07.590
PE. Squad one and squad three,

00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:09.660
we'll push out. Squad two,
you'll fill in behind.

00:02:10.620 --> 00:02:11.620
All right, let's go.

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:24.120
Last year, the US defense
chief announced in Panama

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:25.680
that there would be a revival

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:28.080
of three military bases in Panama.

00:02:28.080 --> 00:02:29.310
There's a long history here.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:33.810
- And fellow citizens.

00:02:33.810 --> 00:02:37.710
Last night I ordered US
military forces to Panama.

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:39.960
No president takes such action lightly.

00:02:41.040 --> 00:02:43.650
There was an invasion,
hundreds, if not thousands

00:02:43.650 --> 00:02:47.850
of people were killed back in
1989 when authoritarian leader

00:02:47.850 --> 00:02:49.500
Manuel Noriega was taken out.

00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:54.300
Jungle training had been going
on in Panama really since the

00:02:54.300 --> 00:02:55.920
1950s

00:02:55.920 --> 00:03:00.250
through 1999 when treaties

00:03:00.250 --> 00:03:05.080
required the US military
to turn over its bases

00:03:05.080 --> 00:03:09.190
and of course turn over
the Panama Canal to Panama.

00:03:11.290 --> 00:03:15.130
So it's been a quarter-century
hiatus from when the

00:03:15.130 --> 00:03:17.980
trainings were last happening to now.

00:03:25.360 --> 00:03:26.950
First and foremost, if called upon

00:03:26.950 --> 00:03:29.860
to serve in any capacity
in a jungle environment,

00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:32.200
that is the first adversary
is understanding how

00:03:32.200 --> 00:03:33.730
to survive and operate there.

00:03:35.050 --> 00:03:37.180
You're dealing with
triple canopy coverage.

00:03:37.180 --> 00:03:39.340
You have a ton of water

00:03:39.340 --> 00:03:41.920
and rain that you're contending
with on a day-to-day basis.

00:03:45.880 --> 00:03:47.380
So it's gonna be a little bit difficult

00:03:47.380 --> 00:03:48.970
'cause maybe a lot of you guys haven't

00:03:48.970 --> 00:03:51.040
utilized a machete, right?

00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:53.170
This is a rare and
unique opportunity for us

00:03:53.170 --> 00:03:55.390
to apply our skills where
you have to learn how to live

00:03:55.390 --> 00:03:57.520
with limited logistics.

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:00.640
I think if you can operate in the jungle,

00:04:00.640 --> 00:04:02.110
you can operate almost anywhere.

00:04:03.700 --> 00:04:05.380
No one I've talked to has said

00:04:05.380 --> 00:04:08.440
that these jungle
trainings mean there will

00:04:08.440 --> 00:04:10.030
be future strikes.

00:04:10.030 --> 00:04:12.790
No one's said that, but I think it's clear

00:04:12.790 --> 00:04:16.030
that the US military are
making sure they're ready.

00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:20.170
There's a lot of jungle terrain
in the western hemisphere.

00:04:20.170 --> 00:04:23.380
Columbia has jungles, Mexico has jungles.

00:04:23.380 --> 00:04:26.440
Cuba has jungles, many other
places too in the Americas.

00:04:26.440 --> 00:04:29.470
It's clear they're training
for the possibility

00:04:29.470 --> 00:04:30.760
of future operations.

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:53.020
This past December,

00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:56.290
the Trump administration published
its new national security

00:04:56.290 --> 00:05:00.430
strategy, and this really came
as a shock to some people.

00:05:00.430 --> 00:05:03.010
It was pretty clear that
there was a pivot to a kind

00:05:03.010 --> 00:05:04.210
of a more muscular,

00:05:04.210 --> 00:05:07.990
more aggressive US
posture toward the region.

00:05:07.990 --> 00:05:10.420
Many people talked about a, a revival

00:05:10.420 --> 00:05:13.150
or reinterpretation of
the Monroe Doctrine.

00:05:13.150 --> 00:05:15.850
This 200-year-old doctrine named

00:05:15.850 --> 00:05:18.220
after the fifth US President, that in

00:05:18.220 --> 00:05:20.620
that time really sought to kind

00:05:20.620 --> 00:05:23.410
of expel European powers
from the Americas.

00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:26.020
Literally a month

00:05:26.020 --> 00:05:30.340
after this new national security
strategy was announced was

00:05:30.340 --> 00:05:34.480
the operation to capture
Nicolás Maduro in Venezuela.

00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:36.460
That followed an unprecedented military

00:05:36.460 --> 00:05:38.080
buildup in the Caribbean.

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:40.450
And of course since then
there have been operations

00:05:40.450 --> 00:05:41.530
in, in Ecuador.

00:05:41.530 --> 00:05:44.080
There's talk of operations in Cuba,

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:46.120
but there is support

00:05:46.120 --> 00:05:49.360
for the United States doing things

00:05:49.360 --> 00:05:52.210
that these countries have not
been able to do themselves.

00:05:53.260 --> 00:05:57.290
There has been kind of an
epic story of human movement

00:05:57.290 --> 00:05:59.690
where people are fleeing bad places

00:05:59.690 --> 00:06:02.810
or places where there is
no economic opportunity

00:06:02.810 --> 00:06:05.090
or really repressive governments.

00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:06.470
So I think that's part of the,

00:06:06.470 --> 00:06:09.050
the argument the Trump
administration is making here in

00:06:09.050 --> 00:06:13.250
terms of why it needs a muscular
approach to Latin America.

00:07:09.290 --> 00:07:11.000
Panama is clearly important

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:15.290
because of this major shipping channel

00:07:15.290 --> 00:07:18.230
that is super important for global trade.

00:07:19.790 --> 00:07:23.510
Something like 5% of global
trade passes through the canal,

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:26.450
around three quarters of
the cargo ships that go

00:07:26.450 --> 00:07:30.320
through are linked to US
imports or US exports.

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:34.640
So it is a major logistical
piece of the US economy.

00:07:35.990 --> 00:07:38.780
You can't have economic
prosperity without security.

00:07:38.780 --> 00:07:41.990
There's two countries and only
two per the neutrality treaty

00:07:41.990 --> 00:07:45.260
that are required to
unilaterally protect the canal

00:07:45.260 --> 00:07:46.430
irrespective of each other.

00:07:46.430 --> 00:07:48.080
And that's Panama and the United States.

00:07:48.080 --> 00:07:49.340
And hopefully nothing ever happens.

00:07:49.340 --> 00:07:51.530
Hopefully all of the things
that we plan, hopefully all

00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:52.820
of the things that we trained for,

00:07:52.820 --> 00:07:55.250
we don't actually ever
have to put them into use.

00:07:55.250 --> 00:07:56.840
But the reality is you have to be ready.

00:07:59.480 --> 00:08:03.980
- My administration will be
reclaiming the Panama Canal

00:08:03.980 --> 00:08:05.900
and we've already started doing it.

00:08:07.580 --> 00:08:10.370
Early on, Trump was
talking about the need

00:08:10.370 --> 00:08:15.370
to retake the canal. On the street level,

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:18.697
this was a very controversial comment.

